***** 📱 Mobile Sales Dashboard – Power BI Project *****

📌 Project Overview
The **Mobile Sales Dashboard** is an interactive Power BI project designed to analyze mobile phone sales performance across different brands, cities, payment methods, and time periods. 
The dashboard provides key business insights through dynamic visualizations, KPIs, and filtering capabilities, enabling data-driven decision-making.

🎯 Objectives
* Analyze overall mobile sales performance.
* Track sales trends across months and weekdays.
* Compare sales among different mobile brands.
* Evaluate customer rating distribution.
* Understand payment method preferences.
* Identify top-performing cities and regions.

🛠️ Tools & Technologies
* **Power BI Desktop**
* **Power Query**
* **DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)**
* **Data Modeling**
* **Microsoft Excel (Data Source)**

📊 Dashboard Features
🔹 KPI Cards
  * Total Sales
  * Total Quantity Sold
  * Total Transactions
  * Average Price
🔹 Interactive Filters (Slicers)
  * Brand
  * Mobile Model
  * Payment Method
  * Month Selection
  * Clear All Filters Button
🔹 Visualizations
  * Total Transactions by Payment Method (Pie Chart)
  * Total Quantity by City (Map Visual)
  * Total Sales by Mobile Model (Bar Chart)
  * Customer Ratings Distribution (Funnel Chart)
  * Total Sales by Day Name (Line Chart)
  * Total Quantity by Month (Line Chart)
  * Brand-wise Sales & Transactions (Table)

📈 Key Insights

* Achieved analysis of **₹769M+ Total Sales**.
* Identified top-selling mobile models.
* Evaluated customer rating trends.
* Analyzed sales performance across cities.
* Compared payment method usage.
* Tracked monthly and daily sales patterns.

🧮 DAX Measures Used
DAX :
Total Sales = SUM(Sales[Total_Sales])
Total Quantity = SUM(Sales[Quantity])
Total Transactions = COUNT(Sales[Transaction_ID])
Average Price = DIVIDE([Total Sales], [Total Quantity])

🗂️ Data Model
  The project follows a structured data model connecting:
* Sales Data
* Product Information
* Customer Ratings
* Payment Details
* Geographic Data

